-- Real Madrid to Make $60.3 Million Bid for Carlos Tevez, People Reports
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-27T12:21:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-27/real-madrid-to-make-60-3-million-bid-for-man-city-s-tevez-people-reports.html

          
          
             Real Madrid will make a 40 million-
pound ($60.3 million) bid for Manchester City striker Carlos
Tevez, the People reported.  
 Tevez’s agents have been working on a deal for if City
allows the player to leave, the newspaper reported, without
citing anyone.  
 City is set to bolster its squad with moves for Valencia’s
David Silva and Barcelona’s Yaya Toure, the People said. Coach
Roberto Mancini is also interested in strikers Zlatan
Ibrahimovic and Edin Dzeko, who play for Barcelona and Wolfsburg
respectively, the newspaper added.  
          
          


  


        